amily Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Johan, Lars, Alf, Nels, Nils, Bjoern, Bjorn, Elof, Evald, Klas, Nanna.","Swedish: ornamental name composed of the elements <i>fors</i> ‘waterfall’ + <i>berg</i> ‘mountain, hill’. Compare   Fosberg   and   Fosburg  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fosberg","meanings":["Norwegian: variant of <b>Fossberg</b>, a habitational name from a farm named Fossberg, from Old Norse <i>fors</i> ‘waterfall’ + <i>berg</i> ‘mountain, hill’.","Americanized form of Swedish   Forsberg  ."]},{"name":"Fosburg","meanings":["Americanized form of Swedish   Forsberg   and Norwegian   Fosberg  ."]}]},{"name":"Adalbert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["older form of   Albrecht ."],"variants":[{"name":"Adalbrecht","meanings":["older form of   Albrecht ."]},{"name":"Adelbrecht","meanings":["older form of   Albrecht ."]}]},{"name":"II.","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adalbert II. von Mörsberg was born in 1065, in Kyburg, Zürich, Switzerland as the son of Adalbert von Mörsberg. He married Mathilde de Mousson about 1096, in Burg, Cottbus, Brandenburg, Prussia, Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died on 28 August 1125, in Switzerland, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1065–28 august 1125":"1065–28. august 1125","1065–1125":"1065–1125","1080–1110":"1080–1110","1102–1179":"1102–1179","1109–1180":"1109–1180","1040–Male":"1040–Surnud","1080":"1080","about 1096":"umbes 1096","um 1109":"umbes 1109","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1040":"1040","1180":"1180","10 NOV 1110":"10. november 1110","28 august 1125":"28. august 1125","1125":"1125","1179":"1179","1102":"1102","ABT 1102":"umbes 1102","1109":"1109","Mörsberg":"Marimont-lès-Bénestroff, Moselle, Lorraine, Prantsusmaa","Heiliga